volume.name: Princess of Power: Journey to Mizar

description: Wally's date could not have gone any worse. He's in real trouble now. He could really use a little help from his friends, but Val and Barry are too busy trying to get high than they are trying to get a clue.

Bloodlust

Chapter 02 of Avaiyo, Vol. 04

Successfully infiltrating the encampment, Emerald Moon now stands before the very heart of the Dark Legion. In their efforts to destroy the Command Center, they've unwillingly become pinned between an impenetrable barrier and an army of undead Neyens commanded by Xaemons of the Dark Legion. With danger coming from all sides, Fayli, Lage and Eyader have only one choice...to engage the enemy.
name: Bloodlust

description:
Open Wounds

Wrongly incarcerated for the mass murders at their concert, Subliminal Torment tries to learn the details and goals of the monstrous members of "Diablo's Scorn." But there's not much time to think when the police station is attacked by thousands of undead zombie/vampire metalheads!
name: Open Wounds

description:
The Balloon Boy's world gets even bleaker when the rumour mill begins churning as neighbours begin speculating about him.

The only ray of light in the boy's life is his growing friendship with the neighbour girl, Tasha.

However, the Balloon Boy's intentions remain unclear.

volume.name: The Boy With A Balloon For A Head

description: Finally! Our hero, Jimmy Watts the tenor sax genius, is clean & sober! No more "bug-juice" for Jimmy. Too bad no one told Slim Watkins, Jimmy's piano-playing bandmate. Can Jimmy stay clean when he drops in on Slim for a jam session? Or will it be more bugs on drugs? Set in a 'bug noir' Manhattan of the nineteen-fifties, Bughouse weaves the story of an ensemble of characters who are essentially human beings with bug-like features, as they dance on the edge of the abyss. Steve Lafler brings alive a lost era of jazz and drugs that evokes a range of emotions and experience rarely seen in comic books.

Twenty years ago, Nuclear and biological warfare ravaged the planet. Now, a sheltered group of humans are forced into the outside world to face the reality of their new lives and the mutated humans who now roam the surface.

This time round it's all about the music! The GalaXafreaks get juiced at The Particle Club to hear their favourite musician DJ Boomertron. But all is not as it seems when the evil Fuzz Muff turns up on the scene!

Never Cross the Dead

There's something strange brewing in Darkport. New new players enter the game but how will it affect The Haunter?
name: Never Cross the Dead

description:
Who Made Who?

The one where they meet an old ally and things go horribly wrong.
In this Episode, our heroes return to Tarquin's family estate and arm themselves with the necessary steampunk equipment to fight back against Bernard the Governor and his evil hospital crew.
As the fish have finally decided to make their move against the vicious heron, a new leader emerges.

The noise of thunder, part twelve.

After saving the former N-CON vice-president Jill Kore, mutated by the mysterious energies that rule Terra and Luna, Tessa has become an enemy for the Community, her parents included. As our uber-voluptuous heroine tries to understand what is the link between Manifest and Terra/Luna with the help of Walko and Demetrius Alpha and Beta, the Community prepares its attack.
name: The Noise of Thunder, Part Twelve

description:
Jack's adventure as the Bearer of The Mark of Aeacus continues. A mysterious stranger appears at the foot of Jack's bed, tells him the secrets of the mark of power that he bears, then tells him he must die. Can Jack's mysterious new powers save him... or would we all be better off if they didn't?

This digital edition adds 25 bonus pages, including Mark Brill's original pencil artwork and a bonus pinup by Briar Hollow artist Terry Blas!

Steam-Powered Avenger

Monsters, robots, and Igor with a shotgun!

What would you do if your brain was put into a massive, steam-powered robot? You'd get revenge on the people who put it there, of course. Now add a case of dynamite, some laser blasters, and a wise-cracking hunchback, and you've got a recipe for something monstrous...

This lightning-paced one-shot from Source Point Press delivers chills and laughs for monster-lovers from age 9 to 999.
name: Steam-Powered Avenger

description:
The one-man anthology is back again with three more short stories. Included in this e-book are...

Shhh/Peaceful - A superhero story told entirely in pantomime.

It's Just A Theory - An educational comic that highlights the distinction between scientific law and scientific theory.

To Everything There Is A Season - A romance comic that deals with the bitter fallout from infidelity.

Also included are an assortment of gag strips as well as comics adaptations of poems by Kabir, Emily Dickinson, Walt Whitman, and WIlliam Blake.

Monster Mosh

Welcome to The Showdown! The denizens of hell are getting geared up for the great race. As The Showdown nears, tensions rise and engines rumble.

Trail Blazing Part Two

The Ravenwood cousins start feeling their efforts are neither as supported or appreciated as the Earl and his guards have suggested as their search takes an ominous turn. The Earl Hadge and his chamberlain lay down the plans to eliminate their unexpected guests but a certain nosy sorcerer discovers their intentions. Meanwhile, a ship by ship search sets in motion a chain of events that threatens to destroy Gabriel and Silvermain's friendship forever.
name: Trail Blazing Part Two

description: Old frenemies and new meet up for 11 fresh comics in VS, issue 5! Check out Football vs Banana, Worm vs Coffee, Shark vs Cheetah vs Man and plenty more!
In issue 3, things continue! There may be questions, there might be answers. What DOES Renee do for a living? What DID happen to Jeremy? When are we going to see more of the cat?

volume.name: Where Do We Go From Here?

description:
CHAPTER 01

In the 60s of the 21st century the last government was dissolved in the name of the Common Interest Corporation. It took twenty long years before someone organized a response... but in the 80s they started to gather, to organise public events and then, when police started shooting into the crowd, they passed the guerrillas.

Now, in 2100, order has been restored. For the society you are a number, a production unit. If you do not want to belong or if you CANNOT belong enough... you are out: a poor outcast or a criminal. It depends on how dangerous YOU are for THEM.
name: Chapter 1: Data Runner

description: Thrust into the far future by his greatest enemy, Adamant arrives in a world that's been transformed into a dystopian nightmare primarily due to his absence from the present. A hero out of time, trapped in an impossibly bleak future, Adamant battles enemies old and new in an effort to return the world to a semblance of the one that was taken from him.

Armadillo Justice follows our heroes, Curly, Billy Bob, and Billy Rock after they crash land on earth. Now these comical space armadillos must defend their new found home from the evil ant empire that plans to colonize the world!

Chapter One: Newborn

'Asphodel' is the breakout Kickstarter success from writer/creator Alex Kane and artist Gale Galligan. A mythic space opera illustrated in lush, gorgeous watercolors and hand lettering, the first creator-owned comic series from Nekyia Studios has been featured in such places as The A.V. Club, Bleeding Cool, GeekMom, and Panels.

The year is 4419. Vic Delany is a two-thousand-year-old veteran of interstellar war returning home after a lifetime of battle in the wilds of space, a battered brainship scarred by the atrocities he's witnessed out among the UNEN colony worlds. Sedna, a cyborg demigoddess and sole administrator of a space habitat orbiting Pluto, is charged with escorting inbound starships back to the Sol system. She also safeguards the gateway to the digital Otherworld: an ancient simulacrum powered by the light of dead and dying suns all across the galaxy, where most of humanity has taken refuge to escape the ravages of war-and achieve immortality.

Alex Kane is the managing editor of the Critical Press, a publisher of books on film and culture, as well as an executive producer of the Star Wars documentary The Prequels Strike Back. A graduate of the 2013 Clarion West Writers Workshop, his fiction has appeared in more than a dozen venues. He has also published essays, reviews, and criticism in Foundation, The New York Review of Science Fiction, SF Signal, and Omni, among other places. He lives in west-central Illinois.

Gale Galligan is a story artist-slash-cartoony person with a BFA in animation from NYU. Her comics have been published in the Game Boss and Transitions anthologies, and she is excited to be contributing to the forthcoming Horizon 2. Gale has also been credited as a production assistant for the excellent graphic novels Teen Boat!, Astronaut Academy: Re-Entry, and Drama. She recently earned her MFA in Sequential Art at the Savannah College of Art and Design. She is the author of the semiautobiographical webcomic Patbird & Galesaur.
name: Chapter One: Newborn

description:
An Overture to Eternal Glory

At the height of Victoria's reign, a scientific expedition to Mars has vanished and the daring rescue mission is now a race against time and space. When control is wrested from fellow scientists and given to a heroic crew of Her Majesty's Navy, can the two groups work together to save the men of the first voyage? Jules Verne meets Star Trek in Ãther & Empire, a tale of adventure, mystery, and terror from Blue Juice Comics!

In Chapter 1 of this 6-part story, a young naval officer is thrust into command during a desperate battle in the skies above the Mediterranean. In his hands lies the fate of not only his ship and crew, but dozens of innocent lives. Will he accomplish the mission? Or doom them all?

Note: The digital edition (3/16/2016) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Chapter 1: An Overture to Eternal Glory

description:
TRUE TALENT

BOB: NON-UNION PSYCHIC

Renegade Psychic. Professional Hairstylist.

Bob Holbreck is pleased enough using his mad hairstyling skills to make the world a little happier, a little prettier, a littler sexier -- even if his great-grandfather thinks he should be honing his awesome psychic powers to join the prestigious Psychic Union. But when an ancient evil returns to kill again, Bob's hand is forced; The City needs a hero, and there's no time to wait for certification.

The legend of BOB: NON-UNION PSYCHIC begins here! And the reviews are unanimous: BOB is "the perfect balance between horror and humour" (Pop Culture Bandit), "a great read for lovers of quirky" (Nothing But Comics), and quite simply "worth your money" (ConSequential). Buy now and see why readers who haven't picked up BOB yet "don't know what they're missing" (Just Saying Asia)!

Beginning the story of how the god, Bron, came to be. With the Sawamii tribe facing complete destruction, Captain Hatchik, the leader of their army, struggles with the tribal leaders, who no longer look to the army, but to a seemingly unreachable deity to save their people.
name: Book I: The God Buried in the Desert, Part I: The Provocation of Hatchik

description: They're best friends, teammates, brothers-in-arms - but that bond is tested to the limit when Falcon targets the Rivas drug cartel, and the Super-Sailor known as the 'Anti-Cap' sets his sights on Sam Wilson! Can Captain America thwart his dark doppelg?nger before Sam Wilson's wings are clipped? Fingers crossed, because there's a Mental Organism Designed Only for Killing waiting in the wings, and nobody's better at stopping him than Cap and Falcon! But M.O.D.O.K.'s not the only big headache on the horizon, with the Avengers about to be Disassembled and all. Is this really the best time for Steve to be kissing the Scarlet Witch? Plus: With the Rivas out for revenge, Falcon may cross a line that could finish one of comics' greatest partnerships once and for all! Collecting CAPTAIN AMERICA AND THE FALCON (2004) #1-14.
name: TPB

volume.name: Captain America and The Falcon by Priest: The Complete Collection

description: Wanting nothing but good things for himself, Doctor L is a man that has his brain running on full steam, yet apparently without brakes. Terrificly terrifying experiments are being made with an exceedingly excessive speeds Tabloids tell tall tales of disastrous failures, but the good doctor L will not abandon his quest to make the world a better place... for himself! 67 pages

There are threats in the world that go beyond our understanding. Beyond our borders. Beyond our world... Agent Benjamin Argyle was trained specifically to deal with such threats because he IS from beyond. As the lone survivor of a crashed alien vessel, Agent Argyle was raised and trained from childhood to become The Dragonfly! Utilizing his otherworldly talents, The Dragonfly becomes the ultimate agent in the dark world of interstellar espionage, warfare and betrayal. He is the border between Earth and the maniacal despots who wish to destroy it.

Raising Dragons is a contemporary fantasy novel that inspires young people to dig deep within to find their God-given strengths and use them to overcome any obstacle. It is both a hair-raising, modern-day adventure and a glimpse into another world-a world of knights, dragons, and fair maidens.

A boy learns of his dragon past; a girl has known of hers for years. They combine their faith, courage, and love to overcome evil, a slayer who seeks to bring an end to dragon heritage, forever.
name: Raising Dragons

description: With Daniel Quaid and his crew declared dead after their space shuttle gets thrown off course by a massive meteor and mission control loses contact, his brother Dane enlists the aid of his retired space marine father, an old friend and weapon specialist, and his technological savvy girlfriend to hijack one of NASAâs most advanced space shuttles to set out on a personal mission looking for answers.

An Exercise in Futility is a daily webcomic, which tackles important and mature subject matter such as oppressive monarchies, crumbling society, time travel, the fragility of mankind and owls. But, more than anything, it's about penguins. Some of them are tall, and some less so.

This first collection showcases some of the best strips from the comic's first almost-one-year of existence. Witness the penguins rise from misshapen blobs to blobs with slightly more direction and purpose, and travel through iconic antarctic moments such as the existential snow-sports, the arrival of the bees, a hard look at bullfighting as a sport and the consumption of brass instruments. Also contains several secret strips seen only by Patreon backers, as well as 8 exclusive Q&A strips with Ethan Catt, creator of the comic!
name: Book 0

volume.name: An Exercise in Futility: The Initial Amalgamate

description:
Fifty long years have passed since my first adventure, the first of many that now I try to tell anyone who would like to know about ...

This story began in a place where everything and anything was possible, a place where the same light had taken its first steps to create everything, even things we know today. In that place there were magical and perfect creatures, as they had to be; here all breathed perfection. So was this place; a paradise called ... ELUMIA.

This is the story of Mel bee, son of the great guardian of Elumia called Borin. These heroes will come soon to rid the world of a threat, which is annihilating every heart of every human being that exists in the world.

Collects Frogman #1-3

He's green, he's wet, he ain't no pet... he's FROGMAN.

Join the Amphibian Avenger as he kicks, punches and shags his way through three crazy adventures. Filled with action, romance, jokes, puns, nerd references and scenes of hardcore sex and violence, it's everything a comic book fan could want and then some.

Lexi's Quest, Part One

In which Lexi and Ander learn that not all is well between their Lands, and Lexi decides that if the grownups aren't going to fix things properly, it's up to her.
name: Lexi's Quest, Part One

volume.name: Lexi & Ander: Adventures in the Middle Lands

description:
Escape from Milan

The artist known as Caravaggio must flee Milan to escape a vendetta before The Inquisition exposes his secret lover.
name: Escape From Milan

description:
Lloyd and his teddy bear, and best friend, Bear do battle in space with the evil Shoal and other wrong 'uns!

This book collects the first four issues of their awesome adventures along with loads of extras (including bear'd up pictures of some of the funders of our successful Kickstarter project)!
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: Lloyd and the Bear: Travels and Tribulations

description:
A new science fiction anthology from Millicent Barnes comics.

This debut issue includes -

Prisoners of Prersao part one by S.J.McCune, an analogue story of stowaways and saboteurs, and The Hunt by Keith H. Perkins, a tale of life and death in the far flung future.

Who is that man hanging from the light pole? How did he get there? Why doesn't anyone seem to care? Join Ed Loyce as seeks out the answers in this comic adaptation of Philip K. Dick's classic story THE HANGING STRANGER.

After many years of relative obscurity in the public domain, Philip K. Dick's THE HANGING STRANGER, originally published in the December 1953 issue SCIENCE FICTION ADVENTURES, is now a brand new thrilling full-color comic book!

volume.name: Philip K. Dick's The Hanging Stranger

description: The first book in the cult graphic novel series, Pictures of You, a story of sex, drugs, rock n roll, and the best friends you'll ever lose.
name: Book One

description:
A young woman who wants her miserable existence to come to an end. Another who wants another shot at life. And a Grim Reaper named Victor. What do these three have in common? They are all connected by Death.

One wants to embrace it, one wants to avoid it, and another is only created for it. But what happens when these three are brought together through a little game that Victor starts all in an effort to help pass the long and monotonous time of eternity?

Follow their adventure when they inadvertently uncover the plot of a secret sect of angels and demons who are planning on a coupe to overthrow Heaven and Hell, join the two domains as one, and destroy Earth!

Following the looting of the National Museum of Iraq in 2003, REBEL CAUSE, a female NSA officer, arrives at a remote U.S. Military outpost in search of a very particular âWeapon of Mass Destruction.â LIEUTENANT TOM BRADFORD and his squad, which includes STAFF SERGEANT JEFFREY âHARDâ KNOX, PRIVATE BOB âSLAVEâ MASTER, and two other Privates are stationed in Eastern Iraq collecting air samples which could aid in their search for chemical weapons. Per Rebelâs orders, Bradford and his men embark on a perilous search for what she, at first, suggests is simply an artifact.
name: The Death of Slave

description:
RubberMan Begins!

Jack never dreamed he would actually become a hero. So when the accident that turned him into a SUPER-hero happened, he decided to embrace this newfound life. And it was fun... for a while!
name: RubberMan Begins!

description:
From Out Of Nowhere

Alberto's life is turned upside down when he is thrown headfirst into a world of deceit, death and mafia.
name: From Out Of Nowhere

description: At their respective performance reviews, lazy minor demon Denzel and high performing guardian angel Hollie are each assigned the same Soul to convert. Let the sparks fly!

Greetings Earthlings! Prepare to feast your eyes on a trio of comic stories chocked full of feral machine hunters, haunting alien lovers and seedy space criminals galore. A daunting late-night collection of thrills and chills from the roller-coaster mind of cartoonist Cee Raymond, Space-Fried Brain Boxes is visceral ride that is certain to leave you wide-eyed, mystified and grinning!
name: Vol. 1

description:
Are You Brave Enough

A divine power saves a transgender woman from her suicide attempt & guides her on a journey of self-acceptance that challenges her to face her inner demons.
name: Are You Brave Enough?

description:
Four stories: A macabre Dark Ages tale. An anti-bullying story. A surrealist love story. An action-packed battle of mutated beasts.

FIRST ISSUE!

VAST EXPANSE #1 is a multi-genre anthology with the following four stories:

A Muslim philosopher travels with his companion through France during the Dark Ages in THE HORROR AT TOURNUS. They encounter a street vendor selling meat of a decidedly macabre nature. Story by Jeremy Scott Nichols. Art by Lautaro Capristo.

In 100% WEIRD, a high school student endures daily bullying from other girls because of her androgynous appearance. She discovers a clandestine school club that exists to protect those like her from the ignorance of her fellow students. Story by Jeremy Scott Nichols. Art by Adrian Bago Gonzalez.

The third story in this issue is PERPENDICULAR LIVES. It is for fans of surrealist art and ideas. A man lives apart from all the world, bound to the west side of buildings, unseen by all. He searches for any chance of love in this odd tale of romance. Story by Jeremy Scott Nichols. Art by J.C. Quattordio.

Finally, in AIN'T AFRAID OF NOBODY, a woman and her boyfriend stumble across a battle between two mutant beasts while trying to experience a relaxing camping trip in the mountains. Will the couple survive, and-more importantly-what will her father think of her man afterward? Story by Jeremy Scott Nichols. Art by Anthony Pugh with grays by Rosa Devine.

VAST EXPANSE #1 is a 24-page, black and white comic book with full-color front and back covers.

Vergil and his son are among orc war refugees hiding in the swamps from violent human raiding parties. They're starving and barely clinging to survival, but rumors of an old wizard living deep in the swamp give them a ray of hope.

When his wife and child are brutally murdered by the evil supervillian known as 'Elementro' --Victor snaps and vows revenge. But,-- What can one average man do against someone who possesses the powers of a demigod?

Ryan Anderson is a porter in St Matthews. His best friend is Mike Woolley, the hospital pathologist. Likeable slackers, they spend their days talking crap until an accident with a scalpel reveals something remarkable.

Ghost of Tomorrow

Mankind has advanced beyond its capabilities to sustain life itself. The Nexus and it's White Cells are the only chance at saving all of humanity from the grips of The West. What's left of the human race will fight in secret wars, where trusting anyone could be a fatal error.
name: Chapter One: Ghost of Tomorrow

volume.name: Die Abenteuer von Tanguy und Laverdure

description:
Every year on Midsummer's Eve, Victor von Doom clashes with the forces of evil in a vain attempt to free his mother's soul from Hell. Only when Doctor Stephen Strange -- Master of the Mystic Arts and Earth's Sorcerer Supreme -- is convinced to join the fight, does the outcome have any hope of changing. But first these unlikely allies must journey to Mephisto's infernal realm ... where they find that the cost of one soul may be more than they are willing to pay!

Collects Doctor Strange and Doctor Doom: Triumph and Torment, Doctor Strange (1974) #57 and material from Astonishing Tales (1970) #8, Marvel Fanfare (1982) #16 and #43.
name: TPB

volume.name: Doctor Strange & Doctor Doom: Triumph & Torment
Die Abenteuer von Tanguy und Laverdure

name: Las Sirenas no se Beben Pescar
